      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benchmarking BGE M3 Embeddings: Objectives and Setup"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Define benchmark goals: measure latency, throughput, and accuracy under simulated API traffic. Use consistent hardware (e.g., NVIDIA GPUs) and tools like Locust or custom Python scripts to generate load. Ensure the environment mirrors production to avoid skewed results."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Methodology for Accurate Performance Assessment"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Structure benchmarks to test various batch sizes and request patterns. Key steps include: 1) Warm-up runs to stabilize model inference, 2) Iterative testing with increasing concurrency, and 3) Logging metrics such as p95 latency and error rates. Validate embedding quality using standard datasets like MTEB."
          }
        ]
      },
